（1） What do you think a true friend is like?</p><p>（2） What will you do if you disagree with your friends?</p><p>(Justification: To help to deepen the understanding of friendship of students.)</p><p><b>Step 5 Summary and Homework (4 min)</b></p><p><b>Summary:</b></p><p>Ask some students to summarize what they have learned today.</p><p><b>Homework:</b></p><p>Write a short passage to introduce your best friend.</p><p>(Justification: To help consolidate the knowledge in this class.)</p><p><b>Blackboard Design:</b></p><p align="center">A good friend</p><p align="center">What’s he/she like?</p><p align="center"><img width="700px" height="116px" src="https://fb.fbstatic.cn/api/tarzan/images/15f0605677e132b.png?width=700" /></p>');
